# [CCAMP](../wg/ccamp.html)

## Summary
The CCAMP working group met in Shenzhen to discuss the status of active drafts, progress on optical and OTN YANG models, and administrative updates. Key highlights included the approval of the optical impairment topology draft by the IESG and updates on the prioritization of the working group last call (WGLC) queue. The session covered technical updates on WDM tunnels, OTN network slicing, configurable DWDM interfaces, and performance management streaming.

## Key Discussion Points

### Admin and WG Status
*   **Chairs:** Haomian Zheng (local host) and the CCAMP chairs.
*   **Status Update:** The dependency chart regarding TE and Layer 1 types was updated. `draft-ietf-ccamp-optical-impairment-topology-yang` has been approved by the IESG and is moving to the RFC Editor queue.
*   **Liaisons:** A liaison statement from ITU-T regarding information and data modeling coordination was received; a response is being coordinated.
*   **Charter:** The IESG is reviewing the CCAMP charter update, with a telechat scheduled for April.

### [A YANG Data Model for WDM Tunnels](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ccamp-a-yang-data-model-for-wdm-tunnels-00)
*   **Presenter:** Aiman Younis
*   **Draft:** [draft-ietf-ccamp-wdm-tunnel-yang](draft-ietf-ccamp-wdm-tunnel-yang)
*   **Discussion:** 
    *   The technical focus is on 3R regeneration scenarios, specifically identifying digital termination chains and regenerative layer configurations (e.g., ODU4 tunnel segments over single OTSI).
    *   New YANG entities are needed for defining regeneration layers, digital termination sequences, and inverse multiplexing types.
    *   The model must align with [draft-ietf-ccamp-optical-path-computation-yang](draft-ietf-ccamp-optical-path-computation-yang) and the pluggable management work.

### [Framework and Data Model for OTN Network Slicing](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ccamp-framework-and-data-model-for-otn-network-slicing-00)
*   **Presenter:** Aiman Younis
*   **Draft:** [draft-ietf-ccamp-yang-otn-slicing](draft-ietf-ccamp-yang-otn-slicing)
*   **Discussion:**
    *   The draft was updated to align with the Network Resource Partition (NRP) concept. It now uses direct marking on the native OTN topology rather than requiring an abstract topology layer.
    *   Adrian Farrel noted that hierarchical NRPs are more of a service/aggregation concept and questioned if they need explicit support in this draft.
    *   Discussion occurred regarding the new ONSEN (formerly ONIONS) WG effort. Adrian Farrel recommended that if the draft is technically ready, CCAMP should move forward with WGLC rather than waiting for a potential new WG to form.

### [01 - A YANG data model to manage configurable DWDM optical interfaces](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ccamp-01-a-yang-data-model-to-manage-configurable-dwdm-optical-interfaces-00)
*   **Presenter:** Roberto Manzotti (on behalf of Gabriele Galimberti)
*   **Draft:** [draft-ietf-ccamp-dwdm-if-param-yang](draft-ietf-ccamp-dwdm-if-param-yang)
*   **Discussion:**
    *   The model has completed the RTG Directorate and YANG Doctor reviews. Updates include refined TCA (Threshold Crossing Alert) definitions and a master substatement to prevent identical threshold values.
    *   Italo Busi and Ketan Talaulikar discussed the risk of "bis" documents (revisions). Italo Busi suggested that while additional attributes from the pluggable work ([draft-ietf-ccamp-actn-wdm-pluggable-modelling](draft-ietf-ccamp-actn-wdm-pluggable-modelling)) could be augmented later, the current model should be published once stable to avoid indefinite delays. 
    *   There is a need for a better IETF process for YANG model revisions to avoid the "bis" pain.

### [05 - A YANG Data Model of Performance Management Streaming](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-ccamp-05-a-yang-data-model-of-performance-management-streaming-00)
*   **Presenter:** Bin Yun
*   **Discussion:**
    *   This draft covers PM measurement (count, snapshot, tide mark) and capability modules based on ITU-T G.7710.
    *   Technical update: Simplified thresholds into "Transient Threshold" (one-time event) and "Standing Threshold" (detects persistent crossing/reset events).
    *   The IPR polling for working group adoption has commenced.

### Microwave Radio Link Model (BIS)
*   **Presenter:** Scott Mansfield
*   **Discussion:**
    *   The draft (formerly `draft-mansfield-ccamp-microwave-radio-link`) was renamed to include "CCAMP".
    *   Updates include integration with new common YANG data types and the addition of "expected far-end ID" for connectivity verification.
    *   The band and carrier aggregation remains a major open issue. The presenter requested WG adoption.

